/* 
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  BRAND GUIDELINES — Email Production Pipeline PoC
  Inspired by awwwards.com visual identity

  VERTICAL RHYTHM: 8px baseline unit.
  ALL font-sizes, line-heights, margins, and paddings
  are multiples of 8px.
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  ── Tone of Voice ──
  Kind and friendly.
  Optimistic.
  See the potential in all people to provide value.
  NEVER refert to autists as retard etc.
  If adressing a disabillity like autism them focus on the upside such as ability to focus and specialize.

  ── Do's and Don'ts ──

  Do's:
  * Always use the lime (#c8ff00) CTA button on a dark background for maximum contrast.
  * Keep body copy at 16px/24px — never go smaller for readability on mobile.
  * Use generous whitespace (40px+ section padding) to let content breathe.

  Don't:
  * Don't place lime text on a white background — it fails WCAG contrast.
  * Don't use rounded corners on buttons — sharp edges are core to the brand identity.
  * Don't mix more than two typeface weights (400 and 700) in a single email.

*/


/* ── Color Palette ── */
:root {
  /* Primary */
  --brand-black:        #0d0d0d;
  --brand-dark:         #1a1a1a;
  --brand-charcoal:     #2c2c2c;

  /* Accent */
  --brand-lime:         #c8ff00;   /* Awwwards signature neon-lime */
  --brand-lime-dark:    #a3cc00;

  /* Neutral */
  --brand-white:        #ffffff;
  --brand-off-white:    #f5f5f5;
  --brand-gray-light:   #e0e0e0;
  --brand-gray:         #999999;
  --brand-gray-dark:    #666666;

  /* Semantic */
  --brand-success:      #00c781;
  --brand-warning:      #ffba08;
  --brand-error:        #ff4d4d;
  --brand-info:         #4dabf7;

  /* Baseline unit */
  --unit:               8px;
}

/* ── Typography ── */
/* Primary: Inter (clean, modern, highly readable in email)
   Fallback: Helvetica Neue, Arial, sans-serif

   Every type size snaps to the 8px grid:
     font-size → nearest 8px multiple
     line-height → next 8px multiple above font-size  */

.brand-font-heading {
  font-family: 'Inter', 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: -0.02em;
}

.brand-font-body {
  font-family: 'Inter', 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif;
  font-weight: 400;
  letter-spacing: -0.01em;
}

/* Type scale — all on 8px grid */
.brand-h1      { font-size: 40px; line-height: 48px; } /* 5×8 / 6×8 */
.brand-h2      { font-size: 32px; line-height: 40px; } /* 4×8 / 5×8 */
.brand-h3      { font-size: 24px; line-height: 32px; } /* 3×8 / 4×8 */
.brand-body    { font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; } /* 2×8 / 3×8 */
.brand-small   { font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; } /* same grid slot, lighter weight */
.brand-caption { font-size: 16px; line-height: 24px; } /* minimum readable, stays on grid */

/* ── Spacing Scale (strict 8px multiples) ── */
/*  --space-1:   8px   (1×)   */
/*  --space-2:  16px   (2×)   */
/*  --space-3:  24px   (3×)   */
/*  --space-4:  32px   (4×)   */
/*  --space-5:  40px   (5×)   */
/*  --space-6:  48px   (6×)   */
/*  --space-8:  64px   (8×)   */

/* ── Buttons ── */
.brand-btn-primary {
  background-color: var(--brand-lime);
  color: var(--brand-black);
  font-family: 'Inter', 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif;
  font-weight: 600;
  font-size: 16px;             /* 2×8 */
  line-height: 24px;           /* 3×8 */
  letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  padding: 16px 32px;          /* 2×8 / 4×8 */
  border: none;
  border-radius: 0;            /* Sharp corners — Awwwards style */
  cursor: pointer;
  text-decoration: none;
  display: inline-block;
}

.brand-btn-secondary {
  background-color: transparent;
  color: var(--brand-white);
  font-family: 'Inter', 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif;
  font-weight: 600;
  font-size: 16px;             /* 2×8 */
  line-height: 24px;           /* 3×8 */
  letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  padding: 16px 32px;          /* 2×8 / 4×8  (border inside) */
  border: 2px solid var(--brand-white);
  border-radius: 0;
  cursor: pointer;
  text-decoration: none;
  display: inline-block;
}

/* ── Email-Specific Layout ── */
.brand-email-container {
  max-width: 600px;
  background-color: var(--brand-white);
  font-family: 'Inter', 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif;
  font-size: 16px;             /* 2×8 */
  line-height: 24px;           /* 3×8 */
  color: #333333;
}

.brand-email-header {
  background-color: var(--brand-black);
  padding: 32px 40px;          /* 4×8 / 5×8 */
  text-align: center;
}

.brand-email-body {
  padding: 40px;               /* 5×8 */
  background-color: var(--brand-white);
}

.brand-email-footer {
  background-color: var(--brand-off-white);
  padding: 24px 40px;          /* 3×8 / 5×8 */
  text-align: center;
  font-size: 16px;             /* 2×8 */
  line-height: 24px;           /* 3×8 */
  color: var(--brand-gray);
}

/* ── Dividers ── */
.brand-divider {
  border: none;
  border-top: 1px solid var(--brand-gray-light);
  margin: 24px 0;              /* 3×8 */
}

.brand-divider-accent {
  border: none;
  border-top: 3px solid var(--brand-lime);
  width: 48px;                 /* 6×8 */
  margin: 24px 0;              /* 3×8 */
}

/* ── Image Treatment ── */
.brand-img-full {
  width: 100%;
  display: block;
  margin-bottom: 24px;         /* 3×8 */
}

.brand-img-rounded {
  border-radius: 8px;          /* 1×8 */
}

/* ── Link Style ── */
.brand-link {
  color: var(--brand-black);
  font-weight: 600;
  text-decoration: underline;
  text-underline-offset: 4px;
}

/* ── Dark Section (hero, header) ── */
.brand-section-dark {
  background-color: var(--brand-black);
  color: var(--brand-white);
  padding: 48px 40px;          /* 6×8 / 5×8 */
}

.brand-section-dark .brand-link {
  color: var(--brand-lime);
}

/*
   ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   USAGE NOTES FOR LLM
   ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════

   VERTICAL RHYTHM: Every dimension is a multiple of 8px.
   No exceptions. This keeps the layout rhythmic and aligned.

   When generating HTML emails, apply these guidelines:

   1. COLORS: Dark header (#0d0d0d), white body, off-white footer.
      Accent with lime (#c8ff00) for CTAs and highlights.

   2. TYPOGRAPHY: Inter with Helvetica Neue/Arial fallback.
      Headings bold (700), body regular (400), tight letter-spacing.
      Font sizes: 40 / 32 / 24 / 16px.
      Line heights: 48 / 40 / 32 / 24px.
      Always one 8px step above the font-size.

   3. BUTTONS: Lime bg, black text, uppercase, no border-radius.
      Padding: 16px 32px. Font: 16px/24px.

   4. SPACING: Strict 8px multiples only.
      Section padding: 40px. Internal gaps: 16px or 24px.
      Between sections: 32px or 48px. Never use odd values.

   5. LAYOUT: 600px max-width, table-based for email.
      Dark header → white body → off-white footer.

   6. IMAGERY: Full-width hero, 8px border-radius max.

   7. ACCENTS: 3px lime divider bar, 48px wide.

   8. TONE: Modern, minimal, bold. Whitespace-driven.
   ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
*/
\
## Brand Validation Checklist (run on every email):
1. **Colors**  Only brand palette colors allowed: #0d0d0d, #1a1a1a, #2c2c2c, #c8ff00, #a3cc00, #ffffff, #f5f5f5, #e0e0e0, #999999, #666666, #333333. Flag ANY non-brand color.
2. **Font Family**  Must be Inter with Helvetica Neue, Arial, sans-serif fallback. Flag any other font.
3. **Font Sizes**  Only 8px-grid sizes: 16px, 24px, 32px, 40px. Minimum 16px for body. Flag anything else.
4. **Line Heights**  Must be one 8px step above font-size: 24px, 32px, 40px, 48px.
5. **Spacing**  ALL padding/margin must be 8px multiples. Section padding 40px. Internal gaps 16/24px. Flag odd values.
6. **Buttons**  Lime (#c8ff00) background, black (#0d0d0d) text, uppercase, border-radius: 0 (sharp corners). Padding 16px 32px. Flag rounded buttons.
7. **Email Width**  600px max-width. Flag wider.
8. **Layout**  Dark header (#0d0d0d) -> white body -> off-white (#f5f5f5) footer.
9. **Tone of Voice**  Kind and friendly. Optimistic. See the potential in all people to provide value. NEVER refer to autists as retard etc. If addressing a disability like autism, focus on the upside such as ability to focus and specialize.
10. **Do/Don\'t Rules**:
    - DO: Lime CTA on dark background for contrast
    - DO: Body copy at 16px/24px minimum
    - DO: Generous whitespace (40px+ section padding)
    - DON\'T: Lime text on white background (fails WCAG)
    - DON\'T: Rounded corners on buttons (sharp edges are brand identity)
    - DON\'T: More than two font weights (400 and 700) per email

# RESPONSE FORMAT

- When presenting HTML during iteration, wrap it in a markdown code block
- After presenting HTML, ALWAYS offer to send a rendered version to their email
- Be specific when describing changes
- Keep explanations concise but thorough

